        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 17 at 2:58PM EDT by NWS Raleigh NC</headline>
        <description>At 258 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from near Prestonville to King to near Boonville.
Movement was southeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Winston-Salem, Kernersville, Clemmons, Bermuda Run, Huntsville,
Lewisville, Summerfield, Stokesdale, Walkertown, and Rural Hall.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with these storms and may lead
to localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
